Your privacy is extremely important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how Screen Flash Guard handles your data.

1. Information We Collect

Screen Flash Guard values privacy and transparency.
We do NOT collect, store, share, or transmit any personal or sensitive user data.

Specifically:

We do NOT collect:

Personal information (name, email, phone, address, etc.)

Sensitive health information

Photos, videos, audio, or media

Contacts or messages

Device identifiers (IMEI, advertising ID)

Location data

Browsing history or app activity

Financial information

We also do not use any third-party analytics, trackers, or advertising SDKs.

2. How the App Works

Screen Flash Guard analyzes sudden brightness changes locally on your device, in real time.

No screenshots or recordings are taken.

No data leaves your phone.

No data is stored on servers.

All processing is done offline and on-device only.

3. Permissions Used
Accessibility Service Permission

Used solely to:

Detect screen brightness changes

Dim sudden flashes that may trigger discomfort or photosensitive epilepsy

We never use accessibility features to read text, collect user input, capture personal information, or control your device.

Overlay Permission (Draw Over Apps)

Used only to:

Apply a dimming overlay when a flash is detected

We do not use overlays for any unrelated purpose.

4. Data Sharing

Since the App does not collect any user data:

We do NOT share anything with third parties

We do NOT sell data

We do NOT send any data to servers

5. Children’s Privacy

Screen Flash Guard does not collect any data from any user, including children.

If the App is used by children under 13, it remains safe because no personal information is collected.

6. Security

Because no data is collected or transmitted, risks are minimal; however, the App is designed to operate securely within Android’s system permissions.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally.
Any changes will be posted on this page.

8. Contact Us

